\begin_layout Abstract
In this paper we prove the uniqueness of the equilibrium states for a class
 of nonzero potentials over geodesics flows on compact rank 1 surface.
 This class includes scalar multiples of the geometric potential and Hölder
 potentials have unique equilibrium states provided they do not carry full
 pressure on the singular set.
 This result partially extends, and is inspired by, Burns-Climenhaga-Fisher-Thom
pson's work 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "BCFT2017"

\end_inset

 on the uniqueness of the equilibrium states for the same potentials over
 geodesic flows on compact rank 1 manifolds.
